  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a targeted W-AR-03 weakener: the governing Requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method, but the supporting ValidationResult was generated by an Activity of type numerical-simulation. The narrative frames the high-fidelity simulation as functionally equivalent to a bench experiment, but the structured activityType field disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod, breaking the formal inference link.",
